<HEADLINE>TRUSTS Monks cautious</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>19</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975142982</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
MONKS Investment Trust's cautious view of the dizzy heights to which world
equity markets have climbed is reflected by the fact that nearly one-fifth of
the fund's #532m of assets are held in cash.
The Edinburgh-based trust yesterday reported an 11.2% rise in net asset value
to 634.1p for the six months to end-October.
Monks convincingly outperformed its benchmark FT World index, which advanced
only 5.0% during its first half, mainly because of the buoyant performance of
the fund's UK equities. The interim dividend was raised 75% to 3.5p, although
this move is aimed at reducing the disparity between the half-time and final
payouts.
n EDINBURGH Income Trust yesterday announced a 7.1% increase in total assets to
#15.2m for the six months to end-October. Net asset value per Ordinary share
rose 8.8% to 43.3p, after providing for the repayment cost of zero-dividend
Preference shares.
</TEXT>
