<TEXT>
Consolation win
ABIDJAN: Two women leaders of Ivory Coast's opposition secured a consolation
victory yesterday, one day after the ruling party's landslide general election
win.
Rebels withdraw
COLOMBO: Tamil Tiger guerrillas trapped inside their northern Jaffna strongold
appear to have begun withdrawing their wounded across a shallow lagoon as Sri
Lankan troops tighten the noose around the town, military sources said
yesterday. ``There are LTTE (Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam) boat movements
mainly at night across the Jaffna lagoon,'' a senior army officer told Reuters.
``They must be evacuating their casualties.''
