<HEADLINE>Papandreou remains stable</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975143004</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Athens
GREEK Premier Andreas Papandreou, in hospital with pneumonia, was put on a
dialysis machine with kidney problems for a second time in 24 hours.
``The premier's condition is stable. He is now undergoing dialysis to help his
kidney function and this may be repeated again tomorrow and the day after,'' a
hospital spokesman told reporters.
He said Papandreou's heart ``is operating adequately'' for now but could not
predict ``what could happen tomorrow or the day after''.-Reuter.
</TEXT>
