<TEXT>
Swimming
SWIMMERS testing positive for anabolic steroids will now face automatic
four-year bans, the sport's governing body announced at a congress in Rio de
Janeiro yesterday.
Retroactive bans will also be introduced, with swimmers found to have used
banned substances to be stripped of all medals and records achieved in the
previous 12 months.
But the FINA congress stopped short of introducing sanctions against
federations whose swimmers fail dope tests, postponing a decision to a meeting
next year before the Atlanta Olympics.
The four-year ban for steroid-use doubles the previous maximum suspension.
Swimmers caught using other drugs will be banned for two years.
