<HEADLINE>Missing girls</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975143037</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
There have been two sightings of Natasha Jones, nine, and Louise Dixon, 10,
both from the Saffron Lane council estate in Leicester, who went missing on
Sunday. Police believe the girls may be sleeping rough on the estate.
In Hampshire, a spotter plane was being used yesterday in the hunt for Mrs
Janet Cooper, 58, who went missing after her dog was killed in a traffic
