<TEXT>
THE STABLES, SHANDON,
NEAR HELENSBURGH
IF you have a good view, you should make the best of it. When an old stable
block in Shandon, near Helensburgh, was being converted into modern living
accommodation it was decided, for the sake of the viewer, to break the usual
rules of interior layout . . .
The result is that the ground floor consists of three bedrooms, a bathroom and
a sauna - while the whole of the upstairs is taken over by a large lounge and
dining kitchen. Measuring 29 by 17ft, the lounge has a central gas fire and, at
one end, patio doors which open on to a terrace which has sweeping views over
Gare Loch to the Rosneath peninsula.
Both the lounge and the dining kitchen have large French doors which open
directly on to views of the loch. Attic space provides the possibility of
further expansion, although local authority consents would be required.
Built of sandstone, the stable block was redeveloped in 1989 and many of its
original stone features preserved. The house has its own private garden and a
shared courtyard. Slater Hogg &amp; Howison is seeking offers over #139,500.
</TEXT>
