<TEXT>
Meekathra Cottage, near Stewarton.
ONCE a simple stone country dwelling, Meekathara Cottage is now a sophisticated
and surprisingly spacious property at the end of a small terrace, standing
among the fields at Stacklawhill just outside Stewarton. Its accommodation
comprises lounge, snooker room, three bedrooms, dining kitchen and two
bathrooms. The lounge has French doors, a polished natural floor, a beamed
ceiling, and a bench built into the window space. The snooker room, also with
beamed ceiling, is just as large (20 by 14ft) and its table centrepiece for
sale if desired. The house has its own alarm system and comes with a detached,
stone-built, double garage. Agent Allen &amp; Harris seeks offers over #139,950.
</TEXT>
