<HEADLINE>Steven's corner - for Gazza?</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>2</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Feature</ARTICLETYPE>
<FLAG>scotlands homes</FLAG>
<GRAPHIC>photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>975143193</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
PAUL GASCOIGNE may have scored a great goal for Rangers against Steau
Bucharest, but he has failed to find the net against CALA Homes. The company
has declined to sell him one of its show homes.
The advantage of buying a show home is that it comes with everything from
carpets to cutlery. CALA is keen to sell him a house, but its show homes have
been declared offside - as they are vital to its marketing campaign.
But if Gazza turns his gaze eastwards, he could pick up a CALA showpiece and do
his team-mate Trevor Steven a favour into the bargain. Steven is selling his
current home, a substantial CALA villa on the outskirts of Edinburgh, to move
nearer to the city centre.
The Corner House, as it is called, is in Kings Cramond at Barnton on the city's
leafy north-western edge. Built in 1989, the house has been upgraded and
extended, ``making this the ultimate house of its type on the market at
present'', says selling agent David Alexander.
The ground floor comprises entrance porch, reception hallway, lounge with
conservatory, dining room, family room, kitchen, breakfast room, a further
conservatory, shower room, and utility room. The stereo system has been
specially wired through the walls.
Upstairs are five bedrooms. The main one has an en-suite shower and steam room.
The attic is partially floored.
The property is part of a small residential development of a number of houses
of similar character varying in size. Its corner location makes it the most
private one.
``The Corner House benefits from being located on one of the best strips of
land,'' says David Alexander. ``The easily-kept gardens are a delight, well
stocked with plants and shrubs giving a variety of colour throughout the year.
The substantial rear garden is in excellent order and the lawn has been
painstakingly lifted, drained and relaid.'' The gardens have lighting to front
and rear.
The house is entered from the road by a 50-metre block paved driveway. It is
being sold at offers over #350,000 by Edinburgh agents D J Alexander. Will
Steven pass it to Gascoigne?
</TEXT>
